Police have launched a manhunt after an armed balaclava-clad gang allegedly attacked and robbed a couple in their home in Tregaeron, Kirkwood, on Monday night. The suspects allegedly made off with two firearms and an undisclosed amount of cash. According to police spokesperson Sergeant Majola Nkohli, the armed robbers allegedly assaulted the terrified couple. “The couple was assaulted and forced into the house at gunpoint,” said Nkohli. “Victims were then tied up while the suspects ransacked the house and stole two firearms, an undisclosed amount of cash and four cellphones before fleeing the scene. “The victims managed to free themselves and alerted their employees, who called the police. Victims sustained minor injuries during the attack.” DispatchLIVE